

## ðŸ”¹ Step 1. Clean old deployment

Remove the previous deployed app from Tomcat:

```powershell
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force "C:\Tomcat\apache-tomcat-10.1.44\webapps\OnlineLMS"
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force "C:\Tomcat\apache-tomcat-10.1.44\work\Catalina\localhost\OnlineLMS" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```

---

## ðŸ”¹ Step 2. Compile Java Servlets

Go to your **project root**:

```powershell

```

Compile all Java files and put class files into `WebContent\WEB-INF\classes`:

```powershell

javac -cp "C:\Tomcat\apache-tomcat-10.1.44\lib\*;C:\OnlineLMS\WebContent\WEB-INF\lib\*;." -d C:\OnlineLMS\WebContent\WEB-INF\classes com\lms\*.java

```

ðŸ‘‰ This creates `.class` files inside:
`C:\OnlineLMS\WebContent\WEB-INF\classes\com\lms`

---

## ðŸ”¹ Step 3. Copy WebContent to Tomcat

Deploy the app by copying your **WebContent** into Tomcatâ€™s `webapps`:

```powershell
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force "C:\OnlineLMS\WebContent" "C:\Tomcat\apache-tomcat-10.1.44\webapps\OnlineLMS"

```

---

## ðŸ”¹ Step 4. Start Tomcat

Run Tomcat:

cd C:\Tomcat\apache-tomcat-10.1.44\bin
.\startup.bat

```

---

## ðŸ”¹ Step 5. Open in Browser

Go to:

```
http://localhost:8080/OnlineLMS/index.html
```

---

âœ… Flow after setup:

* Open **register.html** â†’ Register user â†’ Redirects to **login.html** (alert: registered).
* Open **login.html** â†’ Enter credentials â†’ Redirects to **dashboard.jsp** (alert: logged in).

